			<div class="container">
				<div class="section-header">
					<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
					<p>Common questions about how the EOR hiring model works</p>
				</div>
				<div class="faq-list">
					<div class="faq-item">
						<button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-answer-1">
							<span>Who owns the intellectual property created by the employee?</span>
							<span class="faq-icon">+</span>
						</button>
						<div class="faq-answer" id="faq-answer-1">
							<p>You own all intellectual property created by the employee. The employment contract includes IP assignment clauses that ensure all work product, code, designs, and innovations belong to you, not to InfraDev Consulting or the employee.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
					<div class="faq-item">
						<button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-answer-2">
							<span>Can I terminate the employee if needed?</span>
							<span class="faq-icon">+</span>
						</button>
						<div class="faq-answer" id="faq-answer-2">
							<p>Yes, you have full control over termination decisions. When you decide to end the employment relationship, we handle all termination paperwork, notice requirements, severance calculations (if applicable), ROE generation, and final payments according to Canadian employment law.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
					<div class="faq-item">
						<button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-answer-3">
							<span>What happens if there's a compliance issue?</span>
							<span class="faq-icon">+</span>
						</button>
						<div class="faq-answer" id="faq-answer-3">
							<p>As the Employer of Record, InfraDev Consulting is responsible for all compliance issues. We handle CRA audits, employment law compliance, and any regulatory matters. You're protected from compliance risks because we're the legal employer.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
					<div class="faq-item">
						<button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-answer-4">
							<span>How is this different from using a contractor?</span>
							<span class="faq-icon">+</span>
						</button>
						<div class="faq-answer" id="faq-answer-4">
							<p>The EOR model provides a true employment relationship with full compliance, benefits eligibility, and employment protections. Contractors are self-employed, which can create misclassification risks and limit your control. EOR gives you employee-level control with contractor-level simplicity.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
					<div class="faq-item">
						<button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-answer-5">
							<span>Can the employee work for other companies?</span>
							<span class="faq-icon">+</span>
						</button>
						<div class="faq-answer" id="faq-answer-5">
							<p>The employment contract can include exclusivity clauses if you want the employee to work exclusively for you. Alternatively, if you're comfortable with them working for other clients, we can structure the contract accordingly. You decide the terms.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
					<div class="faq-item">
						<button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-answer-6">
							<span>What if I want to convert to a Canadian entity later?</span>
							<span class="faq-icon">+</span>
						</button>
						<div class="faq-answer" id="faq-answer-6">
							<p>You can transition from EOR to your own Canadian entity at any time. We'll help facilitate the transition, transfer employment relationships, and ensure a smooth handoff. Many companies start with EOR to test the market, then form their own entity once they've established a larger presence.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="cta section">
			<div class="container">
				<div class="cta-content">
